-- Honda Lock Workers Agree on Raise, End Strike, Carmaker Says
-- Liza Lin
-- 2010-06-18T14:23:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/honda-workers-agree-on-raise-at-southern-china-lock-factory-ending-strike.html

          
          
             Honda Motor Co. raised employee
wages at a lock factory in southern China today, ending the
third strike by a supplier to the Japanese carmaker within a
month.  
 Workers, who started their walkout June 9, and then
suspended it June 15 while talks were held with management,
agreed to Honda Lock (Guangdong) Co.â€™s offer, Takayuki Fujii, a
Beijing-based spokesman for Honda, said in a phone interview.  
